# Project Setup Instructions

## Clone the Project

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Aiwan01/specscart.git
cd specscart
```

You will find two directories: `back-end` and `front-end`.

## Install Dependencies

Run the following command inside each directory:

```bash
npm install
```

## Running the Front-end

To start the front-end server, run:

```bash
npm run dev
```

## Running the Back-end

1. Create a PostgreSQL database named `specscart`.
2. Update your PostgreSQL credentials in `config.json` inside the `back-end` directory.
3. Start the back-end server:

    ```bash
    npm run dev
    ```

4. Seed the database:

    ```bash
    npx sequelize-cli db:seed:all
    ```

